1 AN ACT relating to motor vehicle driveaway plates.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 281 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) (a) A driveaway business that holds a proper driveaway certificate issued under
6 KRS 281.630 may apply for a driveaway plate with the county clerk in each
7 county in which his or her principal office or place of business, branch
8 office, sub-agent, or agency is located.
9 (b) A driveaway plate allows a vehicle that has a valid registration of a declared
10 gross vehicle weight to be operated in driveaway service and shall be
11 reusable until the driveaway plate expires or is revoked.
12 (c) The registration fee for initial issuance and annual renewal of a driveaway
13 plate is one hundred fifty dollars ($150) and is payable to the county clerk.
14 (2) Upon receipt of the one hundred fifty dollar ($150) fee, the county clerk shall
15 issue a certificate of registration and one (1) driveaway plate. The county clerk
16 shall furnish each driveaway business that holds a driveaway plate registered
17 under this section with additional driveaway plates upon the payment of a thirty-
18 five dollar ($35) fee for each additional plate requested. Fifteen dollars ($15) of
19 this fee shall be retained by the county clerk for each additional plate issued.
20 (3) A driveaway plate issued under this section shall:
21 (a) Not be used on a vehicle operated on a highway except for the purpose of
22 transporting vehicles in transit;
23 (b) Not be used by tow truck operators transporting wrecked, disabled,
24 abandoned, improperly parked, or burned vehicles; and
25 (c) Be used only by owners, corporate officers, agents, or employees of the
26 business to which the plate was issued.
27 (4) Holders of a driveaway plate shall keep a record of each trip made using a
