6 (5) Driveaway plates issued under this section shall annually expire on December 31.
7 (6) If a driveaway certificate is revoked or not renewed, all driveaway plates issued
8 under this section to the driveaway business holding that driveaway certificate
9 shall be returned to the cabinet.
10 (7) The cabinet shall be responsible for the issuance and cancellation of driveaway
11 plates under this section, and the enforcement of this section, except for the
12 normal responsibilities of law enforcement agencies. The cabinet may
13 promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to
14 administer this section.
15 Section 2. KRS 281.631 is amended to read as follows:
16 (1) No person shall act as a motor carrier without first obtaining a motor carrier vehicle
17 license from the department for each motor carrier vehicle.
18 (2) Application for and renewal of a motor carrier vehicle license shall be made in such
19 form as the department may require. Every motor carrier vehicle license shall be
20 renewed annually.
21 (3) (a) Except for driveaway plates issued under Section 1 of this Act, and except as
22 permitted under paragraph (b) of this subsection, an applicant or license
23 holder shall pay to the department the following annual license fees:
24 1. Thirty dollars ($30) for each taxicab, limousine, TNC, or disabled
25 persons vehicle;
26 2. Ten dollars ($10) for each motor carrier vehicle transporting household
27 goods for hire;
